article.headline: Colgate 80, Quinnipiac 71
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Junior guard Daniel Waddy scored 27 points to lead Colgate to an 80-71 win over Quinnipiac Wednesday night. Colgate made 56 percent of its field goals, including 63 percent in the second half. With the score tied at 9-9, Jon Simon hit a 3-pointer to put Colgate ahead for good. Simon's basket was the start of a 14-8 run that gave Colgate a 23-15 lead with eight minutes remaining in the first half. Colgate extended its advantage to 10 points twice in the first half, before settling for a 36-27 halftime lead. Quinnipiac opened the second half with a 20-10 run moving ahead by 19 points. Later Colgate lead by 22 points before the Bobcats scored 11 straight points to cut the advantage in half. Quinnipiac was able to move to within eight points twice but that was as close as they came. Jon Simon contributed 18 points for Colgate (3-2). Van Crafton and Adam Gonzalez each added 12 points for Quinnipiac (2-3).
